Shocking behavior from a
member of the community’s

01:05:10.755 --> 01:05:12.515
respected clergy.

01:05:12.653 --> 01:05:14.897
It’s expected he’ll
announce his concession in...

01:05:18.418 --> 01:05:21.145
Where did I go wrong, Lord?

01:05:21.283 --> 01:05:23.285
[doorbell chiming]

01:05:32.363 --> 01:05:34.468
- Daryl?
- [Smith chuckles]

01:05:34.606 --> 01:05:36.298
Reverend.

01:05:42.718 --> 01:05:45.583
I’ve been publicly disgraced.

01:05:45.721 --> 01:05:47.619
I may have to move.

01:05:47.757 --> 01:05:50.243
I could face criminal charges.

01:05:50.381 --> 01:05:53.971
Maybe I wasn’t saving the world,
but I was happy being a pastor.

01:05:54.109 --> 01:05:55.800
You know, get the
women’s shelter back open.

01:05:55.938 --> 01:05:57.595
Now I can’t even
do that anymore.

01:05:57.733 --> 01:05:58.872
You finished?

01:06:00.667 --> 01:06:02.255
Have you heard a word I said?

01:06:02.393 --> 01:06:03.946
Yes.

01:06:04.084 --> 01:06:05.913
The Lord chased you out
of your comfort zone, and...

01:06:06.052 --> 01:06:07.881
you’re not happy
with where you landed.

01:06:08.019 --> 01:06:09.607
I’m withdrawing from the race.

01:06:09.745 --> 01:06:13.024
Get my life back... if
my life will have me back.

01:06:15.130 --> 01:06:16.855
No. Hmm.

01:06:16.994 --> 01:06:19.341
You put your hand to the plow.

01:06:19.479 --> 01:06:20.721
There’s no looking back.

01:06:20.859 --> 01:06:22.551
You know this.

01:06:24.518 --> 01:06:26.348
What’s in the bag?

01:06:30.145 --> 01:06:32.078
[sighs]

01:06:39.154 --> 01:06:40.189
Pine cones?

01:06:40.327 --> 01:06:41.949
Lodgepole pine cones.

01:06:42.847 --> 01:06:45.091
They’re covered
in a superhard sap

01:06:45.229 --> 01:06:47.024
to protect the seeds inside.

01:06:48.370 --> 01:06:50.199
Mm-hmm. Okay.

01:06:50.337 --> 01:06:54.307
There can be no new growth
until you expose the pine cone.

01:06:55.687 --> 01:07:00.382
The heat, extreme
heat, like fire heat.

01:07:03.385 --> 01:07:05.042
So they have to burn?

01:07:06.284 --> 01:07:08.148
That’s the upside of wildfires.

01:07:09.046 --> 01:07:11.703
It’s how old
forests are revived.

01:07:13.705 --> 01:07:15.638
Listen, David.

01:07:16.984 --> 01:07:19.401
There are a lot of folk

01:07:19.539 --> 01:07:22.749
that no matter
what color they vote,

01:07:22.887 --> 01:07:25.821
they have lost hope in
the future of our country.

01:07:25.959 --> 01:07:30.067
I see it every day in the
faces of my constituents.

01:07:31.551 --> 01:07:34.105
Same in my congregation.

01:07:34.243 --> 01:07:35.624
They’re wondering
where they fit in

01:07:35.762 --> 01:07:37.798
or even if they should.

01:07:37.936 --> 01:07:40.146
40 million
Christians don’t vote.

01:07:41.492 --> 01:07:44.357
Then another 15 million
aren’t even registered.

01:07:44.495 --> 01:07:45.841
Well, politics is
a dirty business.

01:07:45.979 --> 01:07:47.601
Yeah, so is taking
out the garbage,

01:07:47.739 --> 01:07:51.260
but if you turn your back
to it, things start to stink.

01:07:51.398 --> 01:07:52.675
[chuckles softly]

01:07:52.813 --> 01:07:54.746
- We can no longer ignore this.
- [sighs]

01:07:54.884 --> 01:07:56.748
We have to push
the good of our faith

01:07:56.886 --> 01:07:58.405
into this political process.

01:07:58.543 --> 01:08:01.270
And it is your campaign
that sets the example

01:08:01.408 --> 01:08:03.479
for Christian involvement
in the civic square.

01:08:03.617 --> 01:08:05.688
- What about nonbelievers?
- What about ’em?

01:08:05.826 --> 01:08:07.034
Things are so bad out there.

01:08:07.173 --> 01:08:08.829
We build it right,
they will come.

01:08:08.967 --> 01:08:12.868
In fact, they will
welcome our engagement.

01:08:14.352 --> 01:08:16.216
I don’t know, Daryl.

01:08:17.769 --> 01:08:21.118
[sighs] It just...

01:08:21.256 --> 01:08:23.982
- seems so...
- Impossible?

01:08:26.571 --> 01:08:28.125
Yeah.

01:08:28.263 --> 01:08:31.542
It’s always impossible...

01:08:31.680 --> 01:08:33.647
until it’s done.

01:08:41.655 --> 01:08:43.485
Until it’s done.

01:08:58.258 --> 01:09:00.709
SAM: I think you’re
making a brave choice.

01:09:00.847 --> 01:09:03.263
Which means you
think I’m being foolish.

01:09:03.401 --> 01:09:05.403
Depends on what you say.

01:09:05.541 --> 01:09:08.579
Are you really gonna admit you
knew about the oppo research?

01:09:08.717 --> 01:09:10.167
SAM: Just deny it.

01:09:10.305 --> 01:09:11.754
You have to lie in order
to preserve your image

01:09:11.892 --> 01:09:14.240
- of being honest.
- Did you just hear yourself?

01:09:14.378 --> 01:09:15.931
MYRA: Well, there’s
only one other option.

01:09:16.069 --> 01:09:18.416
You are gonna have to
throw Lottie under the bus.

01:09:18.554 --> 01:09:20.591
Yeah, I’m not really
loving the choices here.

01:09:20.729 --> 01:09:22.524
I’m gonna be straight with you.

01:09:22.662 --> 01:09:24.767
No matter what you say,
it probably won’t work.

01:09:24.905 --> 01:09:26.528
Your chances of
winning this election

01:09:26.666 --> 01:09:29.255
have gone from
slim to nonexistent.

01:09:29.393 --> 01:09:32.430
We were counting on that
third debate to close the gap.

01:09:32.568 --> 01:09:34.777
There’s no reason for
Wesley to let Kane do that now.

01:09:34.915 --> 01:09:36.952
- I mean, they’ve already won.
- Regardless of what happens,

01:09:37.090 --> 01:09:38.712
there’s one thing
that I’m sure of:

01:09:38.850 --> 01:09:40.887
Going forward, we
stop spending money.

01:09:41.025 --> 01:09:43.752
No more ads, no more
posters, no more flyers,

01:09:43.890 --> 01:09:45.581
no more social media spends.

01:09:45.719 --> 01:09:46.996
- Come on.
- Nothing.

01:09:47.134 --> 01:09:48.619
Damage control is
very expensive, David.

01:09:48.757 --> 01:09:51.104
Please, not a penny more.

01:09:52.070 --> 01:09:53.417
It’s almost time.

01:09:55.936 --> 01:09:58.422
[reporters clamoring,
shouts of "Reverend Hill!"]

01:09:58.560 --> 01:10:00.631
DAVID: Hello. Good afternoon.

01:10:00.769 --> 01:10:02.322
Uh, hi, guys.

01:10:02.460 --> 01:10:04.013
DAVID [over tablet]: I, uh...

01:10:04.151 --> 01:10:05.843
I want to thank you
all for coming out

01:10:05.981 --> 01:10:08.259
- on such short notice.
- [sighs, chuckles]

01:10:08.397 --> 01:10:10.641
I also want to extend my
most sincere apologies

01:10:10.779 --> 01:10:12.436
to Senator Kane and his staff.

01:10:12.574 --> 01:10:14.127
I’m not interested
in your apologies.

01:10:14.265 --> 01:10:15.093
DAVID [over tablet]: This
happened on my watch...

01:10:15.232 --> 01:10:16.474
Just withdraw already.

01:10:16.612 --> 01:10:19.305
...so I take full
responsibility.

01:10:19.443 --> 01:10:21.790
All that is left to
say on the matter is:

01:10:21.928 --> 01:10:24.068
I’ve never been involved
in anything like this before,

01:10:24.206 --> 01:10:26.588
and it’ll never happen again.

01:10:27.554 --> 01:10:29.936
I would add that...

01:10:30.074 --> 01:10:32.490
our political system is broken.

01:10:32.628 --> 01:10:35.907
It encourages good
people to do bad things.

01:10:36.045 --> 01:10:38.358
And it’s up to us to fix it,

01:10:38.496 --> 01:10:41.465
{\an8}which is why I’ve decided
to continue my campaign

01:10:41.603 --> 01:10:44.088
{\an8}and drive that message
to the American people.

01:10:44.226 --> 01:10:46.297
He won’t stay dead!

01:10:46.435 --> 01:10:47.885
DAVID [over tablet]: I
would ask that Senator Kane

01:10:48.023 --> 01:10:49.611
honor the terms of
our original agreement

01:10:49.749 --> 01:10:51.475
and meet me for
one final debate.

01:10:51.613 --> 01:10:53.028
- Thank you.
- [reporters clamoring]

01:10:53.166 --> 01:10:54.685
REPORTER: Reverend
Hill! Reverend Hill!

01:10:54.823 --> 01:10:56.203
The information
in the press leak,

01:10:56.342 --> 01:10:58.378
did you know it was fabricated?

01:10:58.516 --> 01:10:59.655
Lottie Jay, has she been fired?

01:10:59.793 --> 01:11:02.451
[clamoring continues]

01:11:02.589 --> 01:11:05.005
I would ask that Senator
Kane honor the terms

01:11:05.143 --> 01:11:06.490
- of our original agreement...
- WOMAN: All right.

01:11:06.628 --> 01:11:08.215
Thank you for staying
with us, Miss Jay.

01:11:08.354 --> 01:11:10.252
DAVID: ...and meet me for
one final debate. Thank you.

01:11:10.390 --> 01:11:12.289
[reporters clamoring over TV]

01:11:17.121 --> 01:11:19.675
[takes deep breath]

01:11:19.813 --> 01:11:22.644
First to the office, and
then to the airport, Tom.

01:11:22.782 --> 01:11:24.197
TOM: Well, why are you leaving

01:11:24.335 --> 01:11:26.164
when the election’s
not even over yet?

01:11:26.303 --> 01:11:27.821
LOTTIE: Yes, it is.

01:11:27.959 --> 01:11:29.823
TOM: Well, Rev
Dave’s not giving up.

01:11:31.584 --> 01:11:34.690
He should’ve never
run in the first place.

01:11:34.828 --> 01:11:36.830
I’m to blame for that, too.

01:11:40.178 --> 01:11:42.698
Look, all I know is running
away never solved anything.

01:11:42.836 --> 01:11:46.357
It just... it just
makes you tired.

01:11:55.884 --> 01:11:57.575
I almost let you beat me.

01:11:57.713 --> 01:11:59.439
I was this close
until I realized

01:11:59.577 --> 01:12:02.200
you’re not worth my
pride or my self-respect.

01:12:02.339 --> 01:12:04.202
Wesley sent the
Kane story to you.

01:12:04.341 --> 01:12:06.550
He was hedging his bets in
case I didn’t go public with it

01:12:06.688 --> 01:12:08.310
because he knew that you would.

01:12:08.448 --> 01:12:10.416
You weren’t doing your
job, so I had to step in

01:12:10.554 --> 01:12:11.969
and do it for you.

01:12:12.107 --> 01:12:13.798
How was I supposed
to know it was a setup?

01:12:13.936 --> 01:12:15.524
You were used,

01:12:15.662 --> 01:12:18.700
and now a lot of people
will suffer because of it.

01:12:18.838 --> 01:12:21.358
I’m sure your
career will recover.

01:12:21.496 --> 01:12:23.394
I’m not talking about me.

01:12:29.158 --> 01:12:30.746
[sighs]

01:12:30.884 --> 01:12:34.854
It happened on my watch,
so I take full responsibility.

01:12:34.992 --> 01:12:37.028
Looks like his
campaign’s gone sour.

01:12:37.166 --> 01:12:38.513
Man.

01:12:38.651 --> 01:12:39.928
Yeah, the Internet
said he was set up.

01:12:40.066 --> 01:12:41.447
- Mm.
- MICHAEL: Goodness.

01:12:41.585 --> 01:12:43.069
We should probably
pray for David, guys.

01:12:43.207 --> 01:12:44.898
Let’s do it.

01:12:45.036 --> 01:12:47.487
God, we pray right now,
Lord, for our brother David

01:12:47.625 --> 01:12:50.628
as he stands in the gap
with so many others, Lord.

01:12:50.766 --> 01:12:52.630
You bless him, Lord.
Give him success.

01:12:52.768 --> 01:12:56.565
Let the results be Your
results, God, and Your will, Lord.

01:12:56.703 --> 01:12:58.222
You would turn this
thing around, God.

01:12:58.360 --> 01:13:00.086
What Satan meant for evil,

01:13:00.224 --> 01:13:01.984
You would make good,
You would turn to good.

01:13:02.122 --> 01:13:04.780
But we pray, Jesus,
in your name. Amen.

01:13:04.918 --> 01:13:06.437
- ALL: Amen.
- DAVID: ...and honor the terms

01:13:06.575 --> 01:13:08.059
of our original
agreement and meet me

01:13:08.197 --> 01:13:09.923
for one final debate.

01:13:10.061 --> 01:13:11.856
That’s all. Thank you so
much. Appreciate you guys.

01:13:11.994 --> 01:13:13.410
I will ask that Senator Kane

01:13:13.548 --> 01:13:15.619
honor the terms of
our original agreement

01:13:15.757 --> 01:13:17.483
and meet me for
one final debate.

01:13:17.621 --> 01:13:19.485
Hill drawing a line in the sand.

01:13:19.623 --> 01:13:22.177
We’ll see how Kane responds.

01:13:22.315 --> 01:13:25.007
I’ll appear weak if
I don’t debate him.

01:13:25.145 --> 01:13:28.079
You’ll appear
confident, unconcerned.

01:13:28.217 --> 01:13:29.943
This is and always has
been your race to lose.

01:13:30.081 --> 01:13:31.289
You don’t understand.

01:13:31.428 --> 01:13:33.499
These people
humiliated me in court.

01:13:33.637 --> 01:13:35.570
I want to make an
example out of him.

01:13:35.708 --> 01:13:37.088
Do you want victory or revenge?

01:13:37.226 --> 01:13:38.987
- I want both!
- It’s too risky.

01:13:39.125 --> 01:13:40.678
Remember, I call the shots here.

01:13:40.816 --> 01:13:41.886
You work for me.

01:13:42.024 --> 01:13:43.612
Make it happen.

01:13:47.789 --> 01:13:49.791
[sighs]

01:13:53.691 --> 01:13:55.175
[sighs]

01:13:59.386 --> 01:14:01.216
LOTTIE: Don’t use a vacuum.

01:14:03.529 --> 01:14:05.807
Lottie.

01:14:05.945 --> 01:14:07.705
I’ve been looking for you.

01:14:07.843 --> 01:14:10.259
I’m guilty of many
despicable things.

01:14:10.397 --> 01:14:13.331
Betraying you wasn’t one of ’em.

01:14:13.470 --> 01:14:16.334
Marc sent the bogus
intel to the press.

01:14:17.301 --> 01:14:19.268
Kind of figured that.

01:14:21.616 --> 01:14:23.480
You should use a
damp paper towel

01:14:23.618 --> 01:14:25.827
to clean up the coffee.

01:14:25.965 --> 01:14:27.553
You sure?

01:14:27.691 --> 01:14:29.658
Pretty sure.

01:14:31.764 --> 01:14:34.007
- DAVID: Ah.
- [both laughing]

01:14:45.363 --> 01:14:46.986
LOTTIE: Thanks.

01:14:48.815 --> 01:14:50.714
[David sighs]

01:15:03.036 --> 01:15:05.107
[David sighs]

01:15:08.559 --> 01:15:11.597
When I told John
I was pregnant...

01:15:13.115 --> 01:15:14.910
...he told me to...

01:15:15.048 --> 01:15:16.947
"take care of it."

01:15:20.329 --> 01:15:22.193
And so I did.

01:15:23.712 --> 01:15:26.922
I’ve been taking care of our
son Christopher ever since.

01:15:32.549 --> 01:15:35.241
Spent years...

01:15:35.379 --> 01:15:39.694
feeling robbed and unworthy.

01:15:44.871 --> 01:15:47.356
I let those feelings define me.

01:15:51.222 --> 01:15:54.432
I didn’t come here to
help you win an election.

01:15:57.884 --> 01:16:00.611
I came to hurt the
person that hurt me.

01:16:06.341 --> 01:16:08.930
Letting go is the
sweetest revenge.

01:16:11.829 --> 01:16:16.178
I am so sorry that I
dragged you into this.

01:16:22.322 --> 01:16:26.326
I didn’t run because you
or Daryl talked me into it.

01:16:27.465 --> 01:16:29.709
I believe God asked me to.

01:16:33.333 --> 01:16:35.473
How do you know it’s God?

01:16:36.474 --> 01:16:39.995
Well, you know
someone long enough,

01:16:40.133 --> 01:16:42.446
you begin to
recognize His voice.

01:16:44.275 --> 01:16:45.794
But sometimes knowing it’s God

01:16:45.932 --> 01:16:48.486
is easier than actually
listening to Him.

01:16:50.765 --> 01:16:54.182
Well, why wouldn’t you listen
to God if you knew it was Him?

01:16:55.804 --> 01:16:57.461
I know, right?

01:16:57.599 --> 01:16:59.739
[Lottie chuckles softly]

01:16:59.877 --> 01:17:03.156
For most folks, it’s fear--

01:17:03.294 --> 01:17:07.471
afraid to fail, afraid
to take a chance.

01:17:09.991 --> 01:17:13.235
But sooner or later, we
all get hit by that storm.

01:17:15.168 --> 01:17:16.722
Hits us at the
worst possible time,

01:17:16.860 --> 01:17:20.208
when we’re already
far out and lost at sea.

01:17:21.416 --> 01:17:25.247
Our first thought
is stay in the boat,

01:17:25.385 --> 01:17:27.974
even though it’s sinking.

01:17:28.112 --> 01:17:30.805
Doesn’t make any
sense, but we hang on

01:17:30.943 --> 01:17:32.841
because it’s what we know.

01:17:34.222 --> 01:17:37.052
And what’s out
there is terrifying.

01:17:39.745 --> 01:17:43.196
But then Jesus walks
across the water,

01:17:43.334 --> 01:17:46.061
then He reaches out His hand

01:17:46.199 --> 01:17:50.410
and He says, "Do not be afraid.

01:17:52.619 --> 01:17:54.311
"Come.

01:17:55.899 --> 01:17:57.694
Get out of the boat."

01:18:00.731 --> 01:18:05.840
Because, well, we know
that... that if we stay in the boat,

01:18:05.978 --> 01:18:10.707
we’ll die and only our
hope in Him can save us.

01:18:14.193 --> 01:18:16.264
God is good, Lottie.

01:18:18.231 --> 01:18:20.199
All the time.

01:18:26.584 --> 01:18:28.448
I’ll call Myra.

01:18:31.935 --> 01:18:36.284
[laughing]: You are gonna
lose this election spectacularly.

01:18:39.943 --> 01:18:42.739
Well, that’s all
the more reason.

01:18:42.877 --> 01:18:44.602
Reason for what?

01:18:45.431 --> 01:18:47.088
To get out of the boat.

01:18:47.226 --> 01:18:49.124
[Lottie chuckles]

01:18:52.541 --> 01:18:53.819
DAVID: This coffee is terrible.

01:18:53.957 --> 01:18:56.235
- LOTTIE: The worst.
- [both laughing]

01:19:23.849 --> 01:19:25.782
{\an8}Good evening. I’m Ron Franklin.

01:19:25.920 --> 01:19:28.198
{\an8}Welcome to this
congressional debate.

01:19:28.336 --> 01:19:32.616
{\an8}This contest is not just
pivotal to our own community

01:19:32.754 --> 01:19:34.825
{\an8}but has far-reaching
significance

01:19:34.963 --> 01:19:36.931
{\an8}for the entire nation.

01:19:37.069 --> 01:19:38.484
{\an8}We’re not just choosing

01:19:38.622 --> 01:19:40.382
{\an8}- a representative.
- [David praying quietly]

01:19:40.520 --> 01:19:43.316
{\an8}We are selecting the
shape of our country.

01:19:43.454 --> 01:19:45.387
{\an8}DAVID: "He will give you
the desires of your heart."

01:19:45.525 --> 01:19:46.803
{\an8}FRANKLIN: Now,
before we begin...

01:19:46.941 --> 01:19:50.289
{\an8}"Commit your way unto the Lord;

01:19:50.427 --> 01:19:52.843
{\an8}"trust also in Him,

01:19:52.981 --> 01:19:55.432
{\an8}and He will bring it to pass."

01:19:56.813 --> 01:19:59.539
{\an8}You praying for a
miracle, Reverend?

01:20:01.127 --> 01:20:03.405
{\an8}- Are you saying you want one?
- [chuckles]

01:20:04.337 --> 01:20:07.409
{\an8}Oh, I’ve seen the numbers.

01:20:07.547 --> 01:20:09.618
{\an8}You’ve seen the numbers.

01:20:09.756 --> 01:20:12.345
{\an8}I’m not the one that
needs divine intervention.

01:20:12.483 --> 01:20:13.760
{\an8}[laughs]

01:20:16.315 --> 01:20:19.421
{\an8}I see someone else
behind that arrogant facade.

01:20:20.871 --> 01:20:23.425
{\an8}I see a man who’s lost his way.

01:20:23.563 --> 01:20:25.703
{\an8}Someone who’s forgotten
what it’s like to lead

01:20:25.842 --> 01:20:27.844
{\an8}with integrity and compassion.

01:20:30.329 --> 01:20:33.746
{\an8}As a matter of fact, I came
here to offer you a lifeline.

01:20:33.884 --> 01:20:37.508
{\an8}All right? A way out.

01:20:37.646 --> 01:20:39.545
{\an8}You concede the race now,

